OL,7,FDecisions over transport are devolved
OL,8,Fto Holyrood, and any work to complete
OL,9,Fimprovements to the road would likely
OL,10,Fhave to come out of the Scottish
OL,11,FGovernment's budget.
OL,13,FTransport Scotland, the Scottish
OL,14,FGovernment's transport agency, said
OL,15,Fthey recognise the "strategic
OL,16,Fimportance" of the A75 and have
OL,17,Fcompleted six major improvement
OL,18,Fprojects on the road, but face
OL,19,F"significant pressures" on their
OL,20,Fbudget for infrastructure.
